3d178729-2559-4f10-ac7d-a3be6e03532c.22e34a47-3b4f-46ad-8658-9fbf4fe1ba07.description=Description\: ------------- Ce flow permet d'ajouter une nouvelle entrée de type "ResultExecution" au rapport d'exécution. Il ajoute une ligne formatée de la manière suivante \: resultExecution¤¤¤¤¤ La nouvelle entrée est ajoutée à la variable globale "VF.reportInfos" (initialisée par le flow "Report.init"). Exemples \: resultExecution¤Exec script "SASC.COLLECT.UNX"¤Collect server information¤srv123¤SUCCESS¤ resultExecution¤Exec script "SASC.COLLECT.UNX"¤Collect server information¤srv123¤FAILURE¤Server cannot be reached Si les caractères de séparation ne sont pas indiqués, l'opération utilisera les valeurs par défaut. Inputs\: -------- in.type (obligatoire) \: Type de l'opération in.object \: Objectif de l'opération in.target \: Cible de l'opération (serveur, fichier, ...) in.status (obligatoire) \: Résultat de l'opération (SUCCESS, FAILURE, WARNING, BYPASS) in.desc \: Informations complémentaire (Message d'erreur en cas de FAILURE, ...) in.separatorField\: Caractère de séparation des champs du rapport in.separatorRow\: Caractère de séparation des lignes du rapport Inputs Examples\: -------------------- in.type \: "Exec 'SASC.DEV.UNX.CollectData''" in.object \: "Collecter informations serveur" in.target \: "srvWin123" in.status \: "FAILURE" in.desc \: "Serveur non joignable" in.separatorField\: "" in.separatorRow\: "" Outputs\: ---------- ou.reportContent \: nouvelle ligne ajoutée Revision\: ---------- 16-10-2017 \: Capgemini - FBI version initiale Configuration\: ---------------- OOSP.HPOO.Report.separatorField (System Property) \: caractère de séparation des champs composant le rapport d'exécution OOSP.HPOO.Report.separatorRow (System Property) \: caractère de séparation des lignes composant le rapport d'exécution 3d178729-2559-4f10-ac7d-a3be6e03532c.63fcea6f-b9e9-462e-b374-8b4a7bc9904f.description=
This operation iterates through a list of values. It is not recommended to modify the value of the "list" and "separator" inputs during the iteration process.

Inputs\:
    list - The list to iterate through.
    separator - A delimiter separating the list elements.
Default value\: ‘,’ (comma) 

Results\:
    resultString - The current list element (if the response is "has more").

Responses\:
    has more - Another value was found in the list and it has been returned.
    no more - The iterator has gone through the entire list. This response is returned once per list iteration.  A subsequent call to the List iterator operation restarts the list iteration process.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.

Note\:
   The position of the iterator in the list is tracked by each step's unique identifier. Therefore, you can simultaneously iterate through the same list from multiple steps.
3d178729-2559-4f10-ac7d-a3be6e03532c.899622d0-9e10-449c-a82e-dc8814f35add.description=
Compares two strings, returning a true response if and only if they contain the same sequence of characters. A null string is considered to be equal to an empty string.

Inputs\:
    string1 - The first string. 
Default value\: "" (empty)
    string2 - The second string.
Default value\: "" (empty)
    ignoreCase - If set to 'true', then the comparison ignores case considerations. The two strings are considered equal ignoring case if they are of the same length and corresponding characters in the two strings are equal ignoring case. If set to any value other than 'true', then the strings must match exactly to be considered equal.

Responses\:
    true - If the two strings are equal.
    false - If the two strings are not equal.
